  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to test the efficacy of the Stroke Counseling for Risk Reduction
      (SCORRE) intervention in increasing accuracy of perceived stroke risk and promoting lifestyle
      behavior change to reduce stroke risk in young adult African Americans.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
